The paper discusses a distributed database management system (DBMS) that targets consistency with availability, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper specifically focuses on hybrid transactional and analytical processing (HTAP) for Internet of Things (IoT) applications, which is a subfield of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses enforcing aggregation constraints as part of transactions, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper mentions resolving conflicts and failures, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of WiSer for IoT applications, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
